  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The first technique described for interbody fusion was the anterior lumbar interbody fusion
      (ALIF).(20) For this technique, the intervertebral disc is accessed through a retroperitoneal
      or transperitoneal approach.

      While the posterior approach was first described by Russell Hibbs in 1911, in the 1950's,
      Cloward (7)popularized the posterior approach for a posterior lumbar interbody fusion (PLIF).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In this study we will try to identify the benefits and outcome of posterior lumbar interbody
      fusion and inter transverse process bone graft fusion.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
